title: Bug 120315 - Display property 'none' not taking effect in new PDF emitter
description: When the display property of an item is set to 'none' in the new PDF emitter, it does not result in the intended behavior.
OB: The label is still visible even though the display property is set to 'none'.
EB: Expected result: The label should disappear when the display property is set to 'none'.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Open the PDF emitter.
2. Set the display property of an item to 'none'.
3. Preview the PDF.
4. Verify that the label is still visible instead of disappearing.
